goto or switch statements. The dispatch_table is constructed at lines 565-604 with labels for each bytecode opcode. The main bytecode execution loop begins at line 757 (run:) and uses the DISPATCH macro (line 210) or switch statement to jump to the appropriate bytecode handler. The opcode_switch label at line 778 is where the dispatch occurs for each bytecode.\n\n## CPU-Specific Dispatch Implementation\n\nEach CPU architecture has its own interpreter macro assembler and template interpreter generator files that implement the dispatch mechanisms:\n\n**x86 (src/hotspot/cpu/x86/):**\n- interp_masm_x86.cpp - Contains dispatch_only(), dispatch_base(), and other dispatch primitives\n- templateInterpreterGenerator_x86.cpp, _x86_64.cpp, _x86_32.cpp - CPU-specific code generation\n- templateTable_x86.cpp - x86 bytecode implementations\n\n**ARM64 (src/hotspot/cpu/aarch64/):**\n- interp_masm_aarch64.cpp - ARM64 specific dispatch implementation\n- templateInterpreterGenerator_aarch64.cpp - ARM64 template generation\n- templateTable_aarch64.cpp - ARM64 bytecode implementations\n\n**PPC (src/hotspot/cpu/ppc/):**\n- interp_masm_ppc_64.cpp - PPC dispatch with dispatch_Lbyte_code() and dispatch_prolog()\n- templateInterpreterGenerator_ppc.cpp - PPC specific generation\n\n**ARM (src/hotspot/cpu/arm/):**\n- interp_masm_arm.cpp - ARM dispatch routines\n- templateInterpreterGenerator_arm.cpp - ARM code generation\n\n**S390 (src/hotspot/cpu/s390/):**\n- interp_masm_s390.cpp - S390 dispatch implementation\n- templateInterpreterGenerator_s390.cpp - S390 code generation\n\n**RISC-V (src/hotspot/cpu/riscv/):**\n- interp_masm_riscv.cpp - RISC-V dispatch with get_dispatch()\n- templateInterpreterGenerator_riscv.cpp - RISC-V code generation\n\n## Method Entry Points\n\n**File: src/hotspot/share/interpreter/templateTable.cpp and .hpp**\nThe template table defines individual bytecode handlers. Each bytecode has multiple entry points based on the TosState (atos, itos, ltos, ftos, dtos, vtos, etc). The entry points are generated and registered into the dispatch table during interpreter initialization.\n\n## Initialization Chain\n\nThe initialization sequence flows through:\n1. interpreter_init_code() in interpreter.cpp -> calls TemplateInterpreter::initialize_code()\n2. TemplateInterpreter::initialize_code() creates a TemplateInterpreterGenerator\n3. The generator's constructor calls generate_all()\n4. generate_all() populates the dispatch tables by calling set_entry_points_for_all_bytes()\n5. Each bytecode's entry points are registered via DispatchTable::set_entry()\n\nThe dispatch table is then accessed at runtime via Interpreter::dispatch_table(TosState state) to obtain the address of the handler for a given bytecode."
}
